This repo maintains its own infrastructure map at [BODY.md](mdc:BODY.md). Read it before making structural changes — actors, scrapers, self-awareness components, expertise files, dependencies, the unified_feed schema.

Then read [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md), [concepts/the_house.md](mdc:concepts/the_house.md), [concepts/self_awareness_loop.md](mdc:concepts/self_awareness_loop.md), and [LESSONS.md](mdc:LESSONS.md).

This is a **public, didactic** repo. All source names are anonymized (`Bank1`, `Expert1`, `Podcast1`, …). Never introduce a real name. CI runs `tools/check_anonymization.py` and blocks the merge on any leak. See [docs/source_naming.md](mdc:docs/source_naming.md).

After any change that affects actors, expertises, scrapers, self-awareness components, dependencies, env vars, or the public API, run `python tools/regenerate_body.py` so the autogenerated sections of BODY.md stay current. The pre-commit hook does this automatically.

Vendor SDKs (`anthropic`, `voyageai`, `lancedb`, …) live inside `m3xa_core/backends/` only. Don't import them from actors, scrapers, or self-awareness components — those use the backend protocols.
